{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b6d172ca-662a-410a-9f7a-a41ef152c45f","content":"Here's what you need to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.v3.runner.mtp` package (xUnit v3) **or**, if staying on xUnit v2, add `xunit.runner.mtp` instead:\n\n   ```xml\n   <!-- For xUnit v2 (your current version): -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"*\" />\n\n   <!-- OR migrate to xUnit v3: -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3\" Version=\"*\" />\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3.runner.mtp\" Version=\"*\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Enable MTP** in your project file:\n\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   # or directly:\n   dotnet run --project YourTest.csproj\n   ```\n\n**Key notes:**\n- `TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport` lets `dotnet test` use MTP instead of VSTest.\n- If you're open to upgrading to **xUnit v3**, that's the recommended long-term path — it has native MTP support and is actively developed. However, v3 has API changes (e.g., `Xunit` namespace → `Xunit.v3`, `IAsyncLifetime` changes).\n- If you want to stay on **xUnit 2.9.x**, the `xunit.runner.mtp` bridge package is the simpler migration.\n\nWould you like help with the actual migration of your project file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"81f913cf-7c2c-43fc-b2d2-081d31005262","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":504,"requestId":"7C47:C87BE:255B940:295F6C8:69F93E21"},"id":"6d40d759-1c0e-40bf-afd7-e54369d9b7ad","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:47:40.462Z","parentId":"b7fec39f-b9cc-40be-811c-ff7d367c50b8"}
